   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>SECTION III The Divine Dispensing of the All-inclusive Christ and Its Functions</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>CHAPTER EIGHT THE DIVINE DISPENSING OF THE ALL-INCLUSIVE CHRIST IN SUPPLYING AND SUSTAINING THE BELIEVERS OUTLINE AND SCRIPTURE READING The all-inclusive Christ being the divine dispensing as the common portion from God to the believers, supplying to them the riches of God in Christ: Being enjoyed by the believers together 1 Cor 1:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>1 Corinthians 1:2b</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>with all those who call upon the name of our Lord Jesus Christ in every place, theirs and ours.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Being what God has called the believers into 1 Cor 1:9.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>1 Corinthians 1:9</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God is faithful, through whom you were called into the fellowship of His Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The all-inclusive Christ being the divine dispensing as the power from God to the believers, supplying and sustaining them in what they are and what they do 1 Cor 1:24a:</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>1 Corinthians 1:24a</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>But to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks Being with a dynamic power.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Strengthening the believers.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The all-inclusive Christ being the divine dispensing as the wisdom from God to the believers, sustaining them in the divine economy and plan 1 Cor 1:24b, 30:</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>1 Corinthians 1:24b</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Christ, God's power and God's wisdom.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>1 Corinthians 1:30</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>But of Him you are in Christ Jesus, who became wisdom to us from God: both righteousness and sanctification and redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Being with counsel.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Affording the saints the strategies.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The all-inclusive Christ being the divine dispensing as the righteousness from God to the believers, supplying to them the righteous way of God 1 Cor 1:30:</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>1 Corinthians 1:30</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>But of Him you are in Christ Jesus, who became wisdom to us from God: both righteousness and sanctification and redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>In procedures and methods.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>That the believers may be perfectly righteous and right toward God, toward men, and toward all things.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The all-inclusive Christ being the divine dispensing as the sanctification from God to the believers, supplying to them God's sanctifying nature 1 Cor 1:30:</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>1 Corinthians 1:30</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>But of Him you are in Christ Jesus, who became wisdom to us from God: both righteousness and sanctification and redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>In position and nature.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>That the believers' spirit, soul, and body may be fully sanctified.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The all-inclusive Christ being the divine dispensing as the redemption from God to the believers, supplying to them daily the divine glory which manifests God 1 Cor 1:30:</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>1 Corinthians 1:30</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>But of Him you are in Christ Jesus, who became wisdom to us from God: both righteousness and sanctification and redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Not only for the believers' life and walk today; But for their future redemption of the body, that their whole being may enter God's glory and may express God's glory and radiance forever.</S>
   </TEXT>
